column1: What is the email of the customer who placed order #1003?
column2: SELECT email FROM Customers WHERE id = (SELECT customer_id FROM Orders WHERE id = 1003);

column1: Do you have Nike Air Max in stock?
column2: SELECT inventory_count FROM Products WHERE name LIKE '%Nike Air Max%';

column1: Which orders were returned and why?
column2: SELECT Orders.id, Returns.reason FROM Orders JOIN Returns ON Orders.id = Returns.order_id;

column1: Whatâ€™s the most recent order placed by Alice Smith?
column2: SELECT id, order_date FROM Orders WHERE customer_id = (SELECT id FROM Customers WHERE name = 'Alice Smith') ORDER BY order_date DESC LIMIT 1;
column9: SELECT o.id, o.order_date FROM Orders o JOIN Customers c ON o.customer_id = c.id WHERE c.name = 'Alice Smith' ORDER BY o.order_date DESC LIMIT 1;
